  1681.     private function __construct() {
  1682.         $localeFileDirectory = PHPEXCEL_ROOT.'PHPExcel/locale/';
  1683.         foreach (glob($localeFileDirectory.'/*',GLOB_ONLYDIR) as $filename) {
  1684.             $filename = substr($filename,strlen($localeFileDirectory)+1);
  1685.             if ($filename != 'en') {
  1686.                 self::$_validLocaleLanguages[] = $filename;
  1687.             }
  1688.         }
  1689.  
  1690.         $setPrecision = (PHP_INT_SIZE == 4) ? 12 : 16;
  1691.         $this->_savedPrecision = ini_get('precision');
  1692.         if ($this->_savedPrecision < $setPrecision) {
  1693.             ini_set('precision',$setPrecision);
  1694.         }
  1695.     }    //    function __construct()
  1696.  
  1697.  
  1698.     public function __destruct() {
  1699.         ini_set('precision',$this->_savedPrecision);
  1700.     }

  1875.     public function setLocale($locale='en_us') {

  1877.         $language = $locale = strtolower($locale);
  1878.         if (strpos($locale,'_') !== false) {
  1879.             list($language) = explode('_',$locale);
  1880.         }
  1881.  
  1882.         //    Test whether we have any language data for this language (any locale)
  1883.         if (in_array($language,self::$_validLocaleLanguages)) {
  1884.             //    initialise language/locale settings
  1885.             self::$_localeFunctions = array();

  1887.             self::$_localeBoolean = array('TRUE' => 'TRUE', 'FALSE' => 'FALSE', 'NULL' => 'NULL');

  1889.             if ($locale != 'en_us') {
  1890.                 //    Search for a file with a list of function names for locale
  1891.                 $functionNamesFile = PHPEXCEL_ROOT . 'PHPExcel/locale/'.str_replace('_','/',$locale).'/functions';
  1892.                 if (!file_exists($functionNamesFile)) {
  1893.                     //    If there isn't a locale specific function file, look for a language specific function file
  1894.                     $functionNamesFile = PHPEXCEL_ROOT . 'PHPExcel/locale/'.$language.'/functions';
  1895.                     if (!file_exists($functionNamesFile)) {
  1896.                         return false;
  1897.                     }
  1898.                 }
  1899.                 //    Retrieve the list of locale or language specific function names
  1900.                 $localeFunctions = file($functionNamesFile,FILE_IGNORE_NEW_LINES | FILE_SKIP_EMPTY_LINES);
  1901.                 foreach ($localeFunctions as $localeFunction) {
  1902.                     list($localeFunction) = explode('##',$localeFunction);    //    Strip out comments
  1903.                     if (strpos($localeFunction,'=') !== false) {

  1908.                             self::$_localeFunctions[$fName] = $lfName;

  1914.                 if (isset(self::$_localeFunctions['FALSE'])) { self::$_localeBoolean['FALSE'] = self::$_localeFunctions['FALSE']; }
  1915.

  1917.                 if (!file_exists($configFile)) {

  1920.                 if (file_exists($configFile)) {

  1926.                             $settingName = strtoupper(trim($settingName));

  1933.                     }
  1934.                 }

  1936.  
  1937.             self::$functionReplaceFromExcel = self::$functionReplaceToExcel =
  1938.             self::$functionReplaceFromLocale = self::$functionReplaceToLocale = null;
  1939.             self::$_localeLanguage = $locale;
  1940.             return true;
  1941.         }
  1942.         return false;
  1943.     }    //    function setLocale()

  1947.     public static function _translateSeparator($fromSeparator,$toSeparator,$formula,&$inBraces) {
  1948.         $strlen = mb_strlen($formula);
  1949.         for ($i = 0; $i < $strlen; ++$i) {
  1950.             $chr = mb_substr($formula,$i,1);
  1951.             switch ($chr) {
  1952.                 case '{' :    $inBraces = true;
  1953.                             break;
  1954.                 case '}' :    $inBraces = false;
  1955.                             break;
  1956.                 case $fromSeparator :
  1957.                             if (!$inBraces) {
  1958.                                 $formula = mb_substr($formula,0,$i).$toSeparator.mb_substr($formula,$i+1);
  1959.                             }
  1960.             }
  1961.         }
  1962.         return $formula;
  1963.     }

  1965.     private static function _translateFormula($from,$to,$formula,$fromSeparator,$toSeparator) {
  1966.         //    Convert any Excel function names to the required language
  1967.         if (self::$_localeLanguage !== 'en_us') {
  1968.             $inBraces = false;
  1969.             //    If there is the possibility of braces within a quoted string, then we don't treat those as matrix indicators
  1970.             if (strpos($formula,'"') !== false) {
  1971.                 //    So instead we skip replacing in any quoted strings by only replacing in every other array element after we've exploded
  1972.                 //        the formula
  1973.                 $temp = explode('"',$formula);
  1974.                 $i = false;
  1975.                 foreach($temp as &$value) {
  1976.                     //    Only count/replace in alternating array entries
  1977.                     if ($i = !$i) {
  1978.                         $value = preg_replace($from,$to,$value);
  1979.                         $value = self::_translateSeparator($fromSeparator,$toSeparator,$value,$inBraces);
  1980.                     }
  1981.                 }
  1982.                 unset($value);
  1983.                 //    Then rebuild the formula string
  1984.                 $formula = implode('"',$temp);
  1985.             } else {
  1986.                 //    If there's no quoted strings, then we do a simple count/replace
  1987.                 $formula = preg_replace($from,$to,$formula);
  1988.                 $formula = self::_translateSeparator($fromSeparator,$toSeparator,$formula,$inBraces);
  1989.             }
  1990.         }
  1991.  
  1992.         return $formula;
  1993.     }

  2067.     /**

  2073.     public static function _wrapResult($value) {
  2074.         if (is_string($value)) {
  2075.             //    Error values cannot be "wrapped"
  2076.             if (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_ERROR.'$/i', $value, $match)) {
  2077.                 //    Return Excel errors "as is"
  2078.                 return $value;

  2080.             //    Return strings wrapped in quotes
  2081.             return '"'.$value.'"';
  2082.         //    Convert numeric errors to NaN error
  2083.         } else if((is_float($value)) && ((is_nan($value)) || (is_infinite($value)))) {
  2084.             return PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::NaN();
  2085.         }
  2086.  
  2087.         return $value;
  2088.     }    //    function _wrapResult()

  2091.     /**

  2107.     }    //    function _unwrapResult()

  2139.     public function calculateCellValue(PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null, $resetLog = true) {

  2143.             $this->debugLog = $this->debugLogStack = array();

  2145.  
  2146.             $returnArrayAsType = self::$returnArrayAsType;

  2155.         if ($resetLog) {

  2161.         } catch (Exception $e) {

  2174.                 $r = array_shift($r);

  2186.

  2339.     /**

  2351.     private static function _checkMatrixOperands(&$operand1,&$operand2,$resize = 1) {
  2352.         //    Examine each of the two operands, and turn them into an array if they aren't one already

  2361.             $resize = 0;

  2367.             $resize = 1;

  2370.         if ($resize == 2) {

  2374.             //    Given two matrices of (potentially) unequal size, convert the larger in each dimension to match the smaller
  2375.             self::_resizeMatricesShrink($operand1,$operand2,$matrix1Rows,$matrix1Columns,$matrix2Rows,$matrix2Columns);
  2376.         }

  2378.     }    //    function _checkMatrixOperands()

  2555.     private static function _convertMatrixReferences($formula) {
  2556.         static $matrixReplaceFrom = array('{',';','}');
  2557.         static $matrixReplaceTo = array('MKMATRIX(MKMATRIX(','),MKMATRIX(','))');
  2558.  
  2559.         //    Convert any Excel matrix references to the MKMATRIX() function
  2560.         if (strpos($formula,'{') !== false) {
  2561.             //    If there is the possibility of braces within a quoted string, then we don't treat those as matrix indicators
  2562.             if (strpos($formula,'"') !== false) {
  2563.                 //    So instead we skip replacing in any quoted strings by only replacing in every other array element after we've exploded
  2564.                 //        the formula
  2565.                 $temp = explode('"',$formula);
  2566.                 //    Open and Closed counts used for trapping mismatched braces in the formula
  2567.                 $openCount = $closeCount = 0;
  2568.                 $i = false;
  2569.                 foreach($temp as &$value) {
  2570.                     //    Only count/replace in alternating array entries
  2571.                     if ($i = !$i) {
  2572.                         $openCount += substr_count($value,'{');
  2573.                         $closeCount += substr_count($value,'}');
  2574.                         $value = str_replace($matrixReplaceFrom,$matrixReplaceTo,$value);
  2575.                     }
  2576.                 }
  2577.                 unset($value);
  2578.                 //    Then rebuild the formula string
  2579.                 $formula = implode('"',$temp);
  2580.             } else {
  2581.                 //    If there's no quoted strings, then we do a simple count/replace
  2582.                 $openCount = substr_count($formula,'{');
  2583.                 $closeCount = substr_count($formula,'}');
  2584.                 $formula = str_replace($matrixReplaceFrom,$matrixReplaceTo,$formula);
  2585.             }
  2586.             //    Trap for mismatched braces and trigger an appropriate error
  2587.             if ($openCount < $closeCount) {
  2588.                 if ($openCount > 0) {
  2589.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Mismatched matrix braces '}'");
  2590.                 } else {
  2591.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected '}' encountered");
  2592.                 }
  2593.             } elseif ($openCount > $closeCount) {
  2594.                 if ($closeCount > 0) {
  2595.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Mismatched matrix braces '{'");
  2596.                 } else {
  2597.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected '{' encountered");
  2598.                 }
  2599.             }
  2600.         }
  2601.  
  2602.         return $formula;
  2603.     }    //    function _convertMatrixReferences()
  2604.  
  2605.  
  2606.     private static function _mkMatrix() {
  2607.         return func_get_args();
  2608.     }    //    function _mkMatrix()
  2609.  
  2610.  
  2611.     // Convert infix to postfix notation
  2612.     private function _parseFormula($formula, PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {
  2613.         if (($formula = self::_convertMatrixReferences(trim($formula))) === false) {
  2614.             return false;
  2615.         }
  2616.  
  2617.         //    If we're using cell caching, then $pCell may well be flushed back to the cache (which detaches the parent worksheet),
  2618.         //        so we store the parent worksheet so that we can re-attach it when necessary
  2619.         $pCellParent = (!is_null($pCell)) ? $pCell->getParent() : null;
  2620.  
  2621.         //    Binary Operators
  2622.         //    These operators always work on two values
  2623.         //    Array key is the operator, the value indicates whether this is a left or right associative operator
  2624.         $operatorAssociativity    = array('^' => 0,                                                            //    Exponentiation
  2625.                                         '*' => 0, '/' => 0,                                                 //    Multiplication and Division
  2626.                                         '+' => 0, '-' => 0,                                                    //    Addition and Subtraction
  2627.                                         '&' => 0,                                                            //    Concatenation
  2628.                                         '|' => 0, ':' => 0,                                                    //    Intersect and Range
  2629.                                         '>' => 0, '<' => 0, '=' => 0, '>=' => 0, '<=' => 0, '<>' => 0        //    Comparison
  2630.                                        );
  2631.         //    Comparison (Boolean) Operators
  2632.         //    These operators work on two values, but always return a boolean result
  2633.         $comparisonOperators    = array('>' => true, '<' => true, '=' => true, '>=' => true, '<=' => true, '<>' => true);
  2634.  
  2635.         //    Operator Precedence
  2636.         //    This list includes all valid operators, whether binary (including boolean) or unary (such as %)
  2637.         //    Array key is the operator, the value is its precedence
  2638.         $operatorPrecedence    = array(':' => 8,                                                                //    Range
  2639.                                     '|' => 7,                                                                //    Intersect
  2640.                                     '~' => 6,                                                                //    Negation
  2641.                                     '%' => 5,                                                                //    Percentage
  2642.                                     '^' => 4,                                                                //    Exponentiation
  2643.                                     '*' => 3, '/' => 3,                                                     //    Multiplication and Division
  2644.                                     '+' => 2, '-' => 2,                                                        //    Addition and Subtraction
  2645.                                     '&' => 1,                                                                //    Concatenation
  2646.                                     '>' => 0, '<' => 0, '=' => 0, '>=' => 0, '<=' => 0, '<>' => 0            //    Comparison
  2647.                                    );
  2648.  
  2649.         $regexpMatchString = '/^('.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.
  2650.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_NUMBER.
  2651.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_STRING.
  2652.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_OPENBRACE.
  2653.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.
  2654.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_NAMEDRANGE.
  2655.                                '|'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_ERROR.
  2656.                              ')/si';
  2657.  
  2658.         //    Start with initialisation
  2659.         $index = 0;
  2660.         $stack = new PHPExcel_Token_Stack;
  2661.         $output = array();
  2662.         $expectingOperator = false;                    //    We use this test in syntax-checking the expression to determine when a
  2663.                                                     //        - is a negation or + is a positive operator rather than an operation
  2664.         $expectingOperand = false;                    //    We use this test in syntax-checking the expression to determine whether an operand
  2665.                                                     //        should be null in a function call
  2666.         //    The guts of the lexical parser
  2667.         //    Loop through the formula extracting each operator and operand in turn
  2668.         while(true) {
  2669. //            echo 'Assessing Expression <b>'.substr($formula, $index).'</b><br />';
  2670.             $opCharacter = $formula{$index};    //    Get the first character of the value at the current index position
  2671. //            echo 'Initial character of expression block is '.$opCharacter.'<br />';
  2672.             if ((isset($comparisonOperators[$opCharacter])) && (strlen($formula) > $index) && (isset($comparisonOperators[$formula{$index+1}]))) {
  2673.                 $opCharacter .= $formula{++$index};
  2674. //                echo 'Initial character of expression block is comparison operator '.$opCharacter.'<br />';
  2675.             }
  2676.  
  2677.             //    Find out if we're currently at the beginning of a number, variable, cell reference, function, parenthesis or operand
  2678.             $isOperandOrFunction = preg_match($regexpMatchString, substr($formula, $index), $match);
  2679. //            echo '$isOperandOrFunction is '.(($isOperandOrFunction) ? 'True' : 'False').'<br />';
  2680. //            var_dump($match);
  2681.  
  2682.             if ($opCharacter == '-' && !$expectingOperator) {                //    Is it a negation instead of a minus?
  2683. //                echo 'Element is a Negation operator<br />';
  2684.                 $stack->push('Unary Operator','~');                            //    Put a negation on the stack
  2685.                 ++$index;                                                    //        and drop the negation symbol
  2686.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '%' && $expectingOperator) {
  2687. //                echo 'Element is a Percentage operator<br />';
  2688.                 $stack->push('Unary Operator','%');                            //    Put a percentage on the stack
  2689.                 ++$index;
  2690.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '+' && !$expectingOperator) {            //    Positive (unary plus rather than binary operator plus) can be discarded?
  2691. //                echo 'Element is a Positive number, not Plus operator<br />';
  2692.                 ++$index;                                                    //    Drop the redundant plus symbol
  2693.             } elseif ((($opCharacter == '~') || ($opCharacter == '|')) && (!$isOperandOrFunction)) {    //    We have to explicitly deny a tilde or pipe, because they are legal
  2694.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Illegal character '~'");                //        on the stack but not in the input expression
  2695.  
  2696.             } elseif ((isset(self::$_operators[$opCharacter]) or $isOperandOrFunction) && $expectingOperator) {    //    Are we putting an operator on the stack?
  2697. //                echo 'Element with value '.$opCharacter.' is an Operator<br />';
  2698.                 while($stack->count() > 0 &&
  2699.                     ($o2 = $stack->last()) &&
  2700.                     isset(self::$_operators[$o2['value']]) &&
  2701.                     @($operatorAssociativity[$opCharacter] ? $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] < $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']] : $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] <= $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']])) {
  2702.                     $output[] = $stack->pop();                                //    Swap operands and higher precedence operators from the stack to the output
  2703.                 }
  2704.                 $stack->push('Binary Operator',$opCharacter);    //    Finally put our current operator onto the stack
  2705.                 ++$index;
  2706.                 $expectingOperator = false;
  2707.  
  2708.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ')' && $expectingOperator) {            //    Are we expecting to close a parenthesis?
  2709. //                echo 'Element is a Closing bracket<br />';
  2710.                 $expectingOperand = false;
  2711.                 while (($o2 = $stack->pop()) && $o2['value'] != '(') {        //    Pop off the stack back to the last (
  2712.                     if (is_null($o2)) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Formula Error: Unexpected closing brace ")"');
  2713.                     else $output[] = $o2;
  2714.                 }
  2715.                 $d = $stack->last(2);
  2716.                 if (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $d['value'], $matches)) {    //    Did this parenthesis just close a function?
  2717.                     $functionName = $matches[1];                                        //    Get the function name
  2718. //                    echo 'Closed Function is '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2719.                     $d = $stack->pop();
  2720.                     $argumentCount = $d['value'];        //    See how many arguments there were (argument count is the next value stored on the stack)
  2721. //                    if ($argumentCount == 0) {
  2722. //                        echo 'With no arguments<br />';
  2723. //                    } elseif ($argumentCount == 1) {
  2724. //                        echo 'With 1 argument<br />';
  2725. //                    } else {
  2726. //                        echo 'With '.$argumentCount.' arguments<br />';
  2727. //                    }
  2728.                     $output[] = $d;                        //    Dump the argument count on the output
  2729.                     $output[] = $stack->pop();            //    Pop the function and push onto the output
  2730.                     if (isset(self::$_controlFunctions[$functionName])) {
  2731. //                        echo 'Built-in function '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2732.                         $expectedArgumentCount = self::$_controlFunctions[$functionName]['argumentCount'];
  2733.                         $functionCall = self::$_controlFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2734.                     } elseif (isset(self::$_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName])) {
  2735. //                        echo 'PHPExcel function '.$functionName.'<br />';
  2736.                         $expectedArgumentCount = self::$_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['argumentCount'];
  2737.                         $functionCall = self::$_PHPExcelFunctions[$functionName]['functionCall'];
  2738.                     } else {    // did we somehow push a non-function on the stack? this should never happen
  2739.                         return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Internal error, non-function on stack");
  2740.                     }
  2741.                     //    Check the argument count
  2742.                     $argumentCountError = false;
  2743.                     if (is_numeric($expectedArgumentCount)) {
  2744.                         if ($expectedArgumentCount < 0) {
  2745. //                            echo '$expectedArgumentCount is between 0 and '.abs($expectedArgumentCount).'<br />';
  2746.                             if ($argumentCount > abs($expectedArgumentCount)) {
  2747.                                 $argumentCountError = true;
  2748.                                 $expectedArgumentCountString = 'no more than '.abs($expectedArgumentCount);
  2749.                             }
  2750.                         } else {
  2751. //                            echo '$expectedArgumentCount is numeric '.$expectedArgumentCount.'<br />';
  2752.                             if ($argumentCount != $expectedArgumentCount) {
  2753.                                 $argumentCountError = true;
  2754.                                 $expectedArgumentCountString = $expectedArgumentCount;
  2755.                             }
  2756.                         }
  2757.                     } elseif ($expectedArgumentCount != '*') {
  2758.                         $isOperandOrFunction = preg_match('/(\d*)([-+,])(\d*)/',$expectedArgumentCount,$argMatch);
  2759. //                        print_r($argMatch);
  2760. //                        echo '<br />';
  2761.                         switch ($argMatch[2]) {
  2762.                             case '+' :
  2763.                                 if ($argumentCount < $argMatch[1]) {
  2764.                                     $argumentCountError = true;
  2765.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = $argMatch[1].' or more ';
  2766.                                 }
  2767.                                 break;
  2768.                             case '-' :
  2769.                                 if (($argumentCount < $argMatch[1]) || ($argumentCount > $argMatch[3])) {
  2770.                                     $argumentCountError = true;
  2771.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = 'between '.$argMatch[1].' and '.$argMatch[3];
  2772.                                 }
  2773.                                 break;
  2774.                             case ',' :
  2775.                                 if (($argumentCount != $argMatch[1]) && ($argumentCount != $argMatch[3])) {
  2776.                                     $argumentCountError = true;
  2777.                                     $expectedArgumentCountString = 'either '.$argMatch[1].' or '.$argMatch[3];
  2778.                                 }
  2779.                                 break;
  2780.                         }
  2781.                     }
  2782.                     if ($argumentCountError) {
  2783.                         return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Wrong number of arguments for $functionName() function: $argumentCount given, ".$expectedArgumentCountString." expected");
  2784.                     }
  2785.                 }
  2786.                 ++$index;
  2787.  
  2788.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ',') {            //    Is this the separator for function arguments?
  2789. //                echo 'Element is a Function argument separator<br />';
  2790.                 while (($o2 = $stack->pop()) && $o2['value'] != '(') {        //    Pop off the stack back to the last (
  2791.                     if (is_null($o2)) return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ,");
  2792.                     else $output[] = $o2;    // pop the argument expression stuff and push onto the output
  2793.                 }
  2794.                 //    If we've a comma when we're expecting an operand, then what we actually have is a null operand;
  2795.                 //        so push a null onto the stack
  2796.                 if (($expectingOperand) || (!$expectingOperator)) {
  2797.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'NULL Value', 'value' => self::$_ExcelConstants['NULL'], 'reference' => null);
  2798.                 }
  2799.                 // make sure there was a function
  2800.                 $d = $stack->last(2);
  2801.                 if (!preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $d['value'], $matches))
  2802.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ,");
  2803.                 $d = $stack->pop();
  2804.                 $stack->push($d['type'],++$d['value'],$d['reference']);    // increment the argument count
  2805.                 $stack->push('Brace', '(');    // put the ( back on, we'll need to pop back to it again
  2806.                 $expectingOperator = false;
  2807.                 $expectingOperand = true;
  2808.                 ++$index;
  2809.  
  2810.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '(' && !$expectingOperator) {
  2811. //                echo 'Element is an Opening Bracket<br />';
  2812.                 $stack->push('Brace', '(');
  2813.                 ++$index;
  2814.  
  2815.             } elseif ($isOperandOrFunction && !$expectingOperator) {    // do we now have a function/variable/number?
  2816.                 $expectingOperator = true;
  2817.                 $expectingOperand = false;
  2818.                 $val = $match[1];
  2819.                 $length = strlen($val);
  2820. //                echo 'Element with value '.$val.' is an Operand, Variable, Constant, String, Number, Cell Reference or Function<br />';
  2821.  
  2822.                 if (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_FUNCTION.'$/i', $val, $matches)) {
  2823.                     $val = preg_replace('/\s/','',$val);
  2824. //                    echo 'Element '.$val.' is a Function<br />';
  2825.                     if (isset(self::$_PHPExcelFunctions[strtoupper($matches[1])]) || isset(self::$_controlFunctions[strtoupper($matches[1])])) {    // it's a function
  2826.                         $stack->push('Function', strtoupper($val));
  2827.                         $ax = preg_match('/^\s*(\s*\))/i', substr($formula, $index+$length), $amatch);
  2828.                         if ($ax) {
  2829.                             $stack->push('Operand Count for Function '.self::_localeFunc(strtoupper($val)).')', 0);
  2830.                             $expectingOperator = true;
  2831.                         } else {
  2832.                             $stack->push('Operand Count for Function '.self::_localeFunc(strtoupper($val)).')', 1);
  2833.                             $expectingOperator = false;
  2834.                         }
  2835.                         $stack->push('Brace', '(');
  2836.                     } else {    // it's a var w/ implicit multiplication
  2837.                         $output[] = array('type' => 'Value', 'value' => $matches[1], 'reference' => null);
  2838.                     }
  2839.                 } elseif (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'$/i', $val, $matches)) {
  2840. //                    echo 'Element '.$val.' is a Cell reference<br />';
  2841.                     //    Watch for this case-change when modifying to allow cell references in different worksheets...
  2842.                     //    Should only be applied to the actual cell column, not the worksheet name
  2843.  
  2844.                     //    If the last entry on the stack was a : operator, then we have a cell range reference
  2845.                     $testPrevOp = $stack->last(1);
  2846.                     if ($testPrevOp['value'] == ':') {
  2847.                         //    If we have a worksheet reference, then we're playing with a 3D reference
  2848.                         if ($matches[2] == '') {
  2849.                             //    Otherwise, we 'inherit' the worksheet reference from the start cell reference
  2850.                             //    The start of the cell range reference should be the last entry in $output
  2851.                             $startCellRef = $output[count($output)-1]['value'];
  2852.                             preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'$/i', $startCellRef, $startMatches);
  2853.                             if ($startMatches[2] > '') {
  2854.                                 $val = $startMatches[2].'!'.$val;
  2855.                             }
  2856.                         } else {
  2857.                             return $this->_raiseFormulaError("3D Range references are not yet supported");
  2858.                         }
  2859.                     }
  2860.  
  2861.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'Cell Reference', 'value' => $val, 'reference' => $val);
  2862. //                    $expectingOperator = false;
  2863.                 } else {    // it's a variable, constant, string, number or boolean
  2864. //                    echo 'Element is a Variable, Constant, String, Number or Boolean<br />';
  2865.                     //    If the last entry on the stack was a : operator, then we may have a row or column range reference
  2866.                     $testPrevOp = $stack->last(1);
  2867.                     if ($testPrevOp['value'] == ':') {
  2868.                         $startRowColRef = $output[count($output)-1]['value'];
  2869.                         $rangeWS1 = '';
  2870.                         if (strpos('!',$startRowColRef) !== false) {
  2871.                             list($rangeWS1,$startRowColRef) = explode('!',$startRowColRef);
  2872.                         }
  2873.                         if ($rangeWS1 != '') $rangeWS1 .= '!';
  2874.                         $rangeWS2 = $rangeWS1;
  2875.                         if (strpos('!',$val) !== false) {
  2876.                             list($rangeWS2,$val) = explode('!',$val);
  2877.                         }
  2878.                         if ($rangeWS2 != '') $rangeWS2 .= '!';
  2879.                         if ((is_integer($startRowColRef)) && (ctype_digit($val)) &&
  2880.                             ($startRowColRef <= 1048576) && ($val <= 1048576)) {
  2881.                             //    Row range
  2882.                             $endRowColRef = (!is_null($pCellParent)) ? $pCellParent->getHighestColumn() : 'XFD';    //    Max 16,384 columns for Excel2007
  2883.                             $output[count($output)-1]['value'] = $rangeWS1.'A'.$startRowColRef;
  2884.                             $val = $rangeWS2.$endRowColRef.$val;
  2885.                         } elseif ((ctype_alpha($startRowColRef)) && (ctype_alpha($val)) &&
  2886.                             (strlen($startRowColRef) <= 3) && (strlen($val) <= 3)) {
  2887.                             //    Column range
  2888.                             $endRowColRef = (!is_null($pCellParent)) ? $pCellParent->getHighestRow() : 1048576;        //    Max 1,048,576 rows for Excel2007
  2889.                             $output[count($output)-1]['value'] = $rangeWS1.strtoupper($startRowColRef).'1';
  2890.                             $val = $rangeWS2.$val.$endRowColRef;
  2891.                         }
  2892.                     }
  2893.  
  2894.                     $localeConstant = false;
  2895.                     if ($opCharacter == '"') {
  2896. //                        echo 'Element is a String<br />';
  2897.                         //    UnEscape any quotes within the string
  2898.                         $val = self::_wrapResult(str_replace('""','"',self::_unwrapResult($val)));
  2899.                     } elseif (is_numeric($val)) {
  2900. //                        echo 'Element is a Number<br />';
  2901.                         if ((strpos($val,'.') !== false) || (stripos($val,'e') !== false) || ($val > PHP_INT_MAX) || ($val < -PHP_INT_MAX)) {
  2902. //                            echo 'Casting '.$val.' to float<br />';
  2903.                             $val = (float) $val;
  2904.                         } else {
  2905. //                            echo 'Casting '.$val.' to integer<br />';
  2906.                             $val = (integer) $val;
  2907.                         }
  2908.                     } elseif (isset(self::$_ExcelConstants[trim(strtoupper($val))])) {
  2909.                         $excelConstant = trim(strtoupper($val));
  2910. //                        echo 'Element '.$excelConstant.' is an Excel Constant<br />';
  2911.                         $val = self::$_ExcelConstants[$excelConstant];
  2912.                     } elseif (($localeConstant = array_search(trim(strtoupper($val)), self::$_localeBoolean)) !== false) {
  2913. //                        echo 'Element '.$localeConstant.' is an Excel Constant<br />';
  2914.                         $val = self::$_ExcelConstants[$localeConstant];
  2915.                     }
  2916.                     $details = array('type' => 'Value', 'value' => $val, 'reference' => null);
  2917.                     if ($localeConstant) { $details['localeValue'] = $localeConstant; }
  2918.                     $output[] = $details;
  2919.                 }
  2920.                 $index += $length;
  2921.  
  2922.             } elseif ($opCharacter == '$') {    // absolute row or column range
  2923.                 ++$index;
  2924.             } elseif ($opCharacter == ')') {    // miscellaneous error checking
  2925.                 if ($expectingOperand) {
  2926.                     $output[] = array('type' => 'Null Value', 'value' => self::$_ExcelConstants['NULL'], 'reference' => null);
  2927.                     $expectingOperand = false;
  2928.                     $expectingOperator = true;
  2929.                 } else {
  2930.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected ')'");
  2931.                 }
  2932.             } elseif (isset(self::$_operators[$opCharacter]) && !$expectingOperator) {
  2933.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Unexpected operator '$opCharacter'");
  2934.             } else {    // I don't even want to know what you did to get here
  2935.                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: An unexpected error occured");
  2936.             }
  2937.             //    Test for end of formula string
  2938.             if ($index == strlen($formula)) {
  2939.                 //    Did we end with an operator?.
  2940.                 //    Only valid for the % unary operator
  2941.                 if ((isset(self::$_operators[$opCharacter])) && ($opCharacter != '%')) {
  2942.                     return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Operator '$opCharacter' has no operands");
  2943.                 } else {
  2944.                     break;
  2945.                 }
  2946.             }
  2947.             //    Ignore white space
  2948.             while (($formula{$index} == "\n") || ($formula{$index} == "\r")) {
  2949.                 ++$index;
  2950.             }
  2951.             if ($formula{$index} == ' ') {
  2952.                 while ($formula{$index} == ' ') {
  2953.                     ++$index;
  2954.                 }
  2955.                 //    If we're expecting an operator, but only have a space between the previous and next operands (and both are
  2956.                 //        Cell References) then we have an INTERSECTION operator
  2957. //                echo 'Possible Intersect Operator<br />';
  2958.                 if (($expectingOperator) && (preg_match('/^'.self::CALCULATION_REGEXP_CELLREF.'.*/Ui', substr($formula, $index), $match)) &&
  2959.                     ($output[count($output)-1]['type'] == 'Cell Reference')) {
  2960. //                    echo 'Element is an Intersect Operator<br />';
  2961.                     while($stack->count() > 0 &&
  2962.                         ($o2 = $stack->last()) &&
  2963.                         isset(self::$_operators[$o2['value']]) &&
  2964.                         @($operatorAssociativity[$opCharacter] ? $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] < $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']] : $operatorPrecedence[$opCharacter] <= $operatorPrecedence[$o2['value']])) {
  2965.                         $output[] = $stack->pop();                                //    Swap operands and higher precedence operators from the stack to the output
  2966.                     }
  2967.                     $stack->push('Binary Operator','|');    //    Put an Intersect Operator on the stack
  2968.                     $expectingOperator = false;
  2969.                 }
  2970.             }
  2971.         }
  2972.  
  2973.         while (!is_null($op = $stack->pop())) {    // pop everything off the stack and push onto output
  2974.             if ($opCharacter['value'] == '(') return $this->_raiseFormulaError("Formula Error: Expecting ')'");    // if there are any opening braces on the stack, then braces were unbalanced
  2975.             $output[] = $op;
  2976.         }
  2977.         return $output;
  2978.     }    //    function _parseFormula()
  2979.  
  2980.  
  2981.     // evaluate postfix notation
  2982.     private function _processTokenStack($tokens, $cellID = null, PHPExcel_Cell $pCell = null) {
  2983.         if ($tokens == false) return false;
  2984.  
  2985.         //    If we're using cell caching, then $pCell may well be flushed back to the cache (which detaches the parent worksheet),
  2986.         //        so we store the parent worksheet so that we can re-attach it when necessary
  2987.         $pCellParent = (!is_null($pCell)) ? $pCell->getParent() : null;
  2988.         $stack = new PHPExcel_Token_Stack;
  2989.  
  2990.         //    Loop through each token in turn
  2991.         foreach ($tokens as $tokenData) {
  2992. //            print_r($tokenData);
  2993. //            echo '<br />';
  2994.             $token = $tokenData['value'];
  2995. //            echo '<b>Token is '.$token.'</b><br />';
  2996.             // if the token is a binary operator, pop the top two values off the stack, do the operation, and push the result back on the stack
  2997.             if (isset(self::$_binaryOperators[$token])) {
  2998. //                echo 'Token is a binary operator<br />';
  2999.                 //    We must have two operands, error if we don't
  3000.                 if (is_null($operand2Data = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  3001.                 if (is_null($operand1Data = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  3002.                 //    Log what we're doing
  3003.                 $operand1 = $operand1Data['value'];
  3004.                 $operand2 = $operand2Data['value'];
  3005.                 if ($token == ':') {
  3006.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Range '.$this->_showValue($operand1Data['reference']).$token.$this->_showValue($operand2Data['reference']));
  3007.                 } else {
  3008.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.$this->_showValue($operand1).' '.$token.' '.$this->_showValue($operand2));
  3009.                 }
  3010.                 //    Process the operation in the appropriate manner
  3011.                 switch ($token) {
  3012.                     //    Comparison (Boolean) Operators
  3013.                     case '>'    :            //    Greater than
  3014.                     case '<'    :            //    Less than
  3015.                     case '>='    :            //    Greater than or Equal to
  3016.                     case '<='    :            //    Less than or Equal to
  3017.                     case '='    :            //    Equality
  3018.                     case '<>'    :            //    Inequality
  3019.                         $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,$stack);
  3020.                         break;
  3021.                     //    Binary Operators
  3022.                     case ':'    :            //    Range
  3023.                         $sheet1 = $sheet2 = '';
  3024.                         if (strpos($operand1Data['reference'],'!') !== false) {
  3025.                             list($sheet1,$operand1Data['reference']) = explode('!',$operand1Data['reference']);
  3026.                         } else {
  3027.                             $sheet1 = (!is_null($pCellParent)) ? $pCellParent->getTitle() : '';
  3028.                         }
  3029.                         if (strpos($operand2Data['reference'],'!') !== false) {
  3030.                             list($sheet2,$operand2Data['reference']) = explode('!',$operand2Data['reference']);
  3031.                         } else {
  3032.                             $sheet2 = $sheet1;
  3033.                         }
  3034.                         if ($sheet1 == $sheet2) {
  3035.                             if (is_null($operand1Data['reference'])) {
  3036.                                 if ((trim($operand1Data['value']) != '') && (is_numeric($operand1Data['value']))) {
  3037.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$operand1Data['value'];
  3038.                                 } elseif (trim($operand1Data['reference']) == '') {
  3039.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $pCell->getCoordinate();
  3040.                                 } else {
  3041.                                     $operand1Data['reference'] = $operand1Data['value'].$pCell->getRow();
  3042.                                 }
  3043.                             }
  3044.                             if (is_null($operand2Data['reference'])) {
  3045.                                 if ((trim($operand2Data['value']) != '') && (is_numeric($operand2Data['value']))) {
  3046.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $pCell->getColumn().$operand2Data['value'];
  3047.                                 } elseif (trim($operand2Data['reference']) == '') {
  3048.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $pCell->getCoordinate();
  3049.                                 } else {
  3050.                                     $operand2Data['reference'] = $operand2Data['value'].$pCell->getRow();
  3051.                                 }
  3052.                             }
  3053.  
  3054.                             $oData = array_merge(explode(':',$operand1Data['reference']),explode(':',$operand2Data['reference']));
  3055.                             $oCol = $oRow = array();
  3056.                             foreach($oData as $oDatum) {
  3057.                                 $oCR = PHPExcel_Cell::coordinateFromString($oDatum);
  3058.                                 $oCol[] = PHPExcel_Cell::columnIndexFromString($oCR[0]) - 1;
  3059.                                 $oRow[] = $oCR[1];
  3060.                             }
  3061.                             $cellRef = PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(min($oCol)).min($oRow).':'.PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(max($oCol)).max($oRow);
  3062.                             if (!is_null($pCellParent)) {
  3063.                                 $cellValue = $this->extractCellRange($cellRef, $pCellParent->getParent()->getSheetByName($sheet1), false);
  3064.                             } else {
  3065.                                 return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Unable to access Cell Reference');
  3066.                             }
  3067.                             $stack->push('Cell Reference',$cellValue,$cellRef);
  3068.                         } else {
  3069.                             $stack->push('Error',PHPExcel_Calculation_Functions::REF(),null);
  3070.                         }
  3071.  
  3072.                         break;
  3073.                     case '+'    :            //    Addition
  3074.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'plusEquals',$stack);
  3075.                         break;
  3076.                     case '-'    :            //    Subtraction
  3077.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'minusEquals',$stack);
  3078.                         break;
  3079.                     case '*'    :            //    Multiplication
  3080.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'arrayTimesEquals',$stack);
  3081.                         break;
  3082.                     case '/'    :            //    Division
  3083.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'arrayRightDivide',$stack);
  3084.                         break;
  3085.                     case '^'    :            //    Exponential
  3086.                         $this->_executeNumericBinaryOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$token,'power',$stack);
  3087.                         break;
  3088.                     case '&'    :            //    Concatenation
  3089.                         //    If either of the operands is a matrix, we need to treat them both as matrices
  3090.                         //        (converting the other operand to a matrix if need be); then perform the required
  3091.                         //        matrix operation
  3092.                         if (is_bool($operand1)) {
  3093.                             $operand1 = ($operand1) ? self::$_localeBoolean['TRUE'] : self::$_localeBoolean['FALSE'];
  3094.                         }
  3095.                         if (is_bool($operand2)) {
  3096.                             $operand2 = ($operand2) ? self::$_localeBoolean['TRUE'] : self::$_localeBoolean['FALSE'];
  3097.                         }
  3098.                         if ((is_array($operand1)) || (is_array($operand2))) {
  3099.                             //    Ensure that both operands are arrays/matrices
  3100.                             self::_checkMatrixOperands($operand1,$operand2,2);
  3101.                             try {
  3102.                                 //    Convert operand 1 from a PHP array to a matrix
  3103.                                 $matrix = new PHPExcel_Shared_JAMA_Matrix($operand1);
  3104.                                 //    Perform the required operation against the operand 1 matrix, passing in operand 2
  3105.                                 $matrixResult = $matrix->concat($operand2);
  3106.                                 $result = $matrixResult->getArray();
  3107.                             } catch (Exception $ex) {
  3108.                                 $this->_writeDebug('JAMA Matrix Exception: '.$ex->getMessage());
  3109.                                 $result = '#VALUE!';
  3110.                             }
  3111.                         } else {
  3112.                             $result = '"'.str_replace('""','"',self::_unwrapResult($operand1,'"').self::_unwrapResult($operand2,'"')).'"';
  3113.                         }
  3114.                         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.$this->_showTypeDetails($result));
  3115.                         $stack->push('Value',$result);
  3116.                         break;
  3117.                     case '|'    :            //    Intersect
  3118.                         $rowIntersect = array_intersect_key($operand1,$operand2);
  3119.                         $cellIntersect = $oCol = $oRow = array();
  3120.                         foreach(array_keys($rowIntersect) as $row) {
  3121.                             $oRow[] = $row;
  3122.                             foreach($rowIntersect[$row] as $col => $data) {
  3123.                                 $oCol[] = PHPExcel_Cell::columnIndexFromString($col) - 1;
  3124.                                 $cellIntersect[$row] = array_intersect_key($operand1[$row],$operand2[$row]);
  3125.                             }
  3126.                         }
  3127.                         $cellRef = PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(min($oCol)).min($oRow).':'.PHPExcel_Cell::stringFromColumnIndex(max($oCol)).max($oRow);
  3128.                         $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.$this->_showTypeDetails($cellIntersect));
  3129.                         $stack->push('Value',$cellIntersect,$cellRef);
  3130.                         break;
  3131.                 }
  3132.  
  3133.             // if the token is a unary operator, pop one value off the stack, do the operation, and push it back on
  3134.             } elseif (($token === '~') || ($token === '%')) {
  3135. //                echo 'Token is a unary operator<br />';
  3136.                 if (is_null($arg = $stack->pop())) return $this->_raiseFormulaError('Internal error - Operand value missing from stack');
  3137.                 $arg = $arg['value'];
  3138.                 if ($token === '~') {
  3139. //                    echo 'Token is a negation operator<br />';
  3140.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating Negation of '.$this->_showValue($arg));
  3141.                     $multiplier = -1;
  3142.                 } else {
  3143. //                    echo 'Token is a percentile operator<br />';

  3368.     private function _validateBinaryOperand($cellID,&$operand,&$stack) {
  3369.         //    Numbers, matrices and booleans can pass straight through, as they're already valid
  3370.         if (is_string($operand)) {
  3371.             //    We only need special validations for the operand if it is a string
  3372.             //    Start by stripping off the quotation marks we use to identify true excel string values internally
  3373.             if ($operand > '' && $operand{0} == '"') { $operand = self::_unwrapResult($operand); }
  3374.             //    If the string is a numeric value, we treat it as a numeric, so no further testing
  3375.             if (!is_numeric($operand)) {
  3376.                 //    If not a numeric, test to see if the value is an Excel error, and so can't be used in normal binary operations
  3377.                 if ($operand > '' && $operand{0} == '#') {
  3378.                     $stack->push('Value', $operand);
  3379.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.$this->_showTypeDetails($operand));
  3380.                     return false;
  3381.                 } elseif (!PHPExcel_Shared_String::convertToNumberIfFraction($operand)) {
  3382.                     //    If not a numeric or a fraction, then it's a text string, and so can't be used in mathematical binary operations
  3383.                     $stack->push('Value', '#VALUE!');
  3384.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is a '.$this->_showTypeDetails('#VALUE!'));
  3385.                     return false;
  3386.                 }
  3387.             }
  3388.         }
  3389.  
  3390.         //    return a true if the value of the operand is one that we can use in normal binary operations
  3391.         return true;
  3392.     }    //    function _validateBinaryOperand()

  3395.     private function _executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operand2,$operation,&$stack,$recursingArrays=false) {
  3396.         //    If we're dealing with matrix operations, we want a matrix result
  3397.         if ((is_array($operand1)) || (is_array($operand2))) {
  3398.             $result = array();
  3399.             if ((is_array($operand1)) && (!is_array($operand2))) {
  3400.                 foreach($operand1 as $x => $operandData) {
  3401.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.$this->_showValue($operandData).' '.$operation.' '.$this->_showValue($operand2));
  3402.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operandData,$operand2,$operation,$stack);
  3403.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  3404.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  3405.                 }
  3406.             } elseif ((!is_array($operand1)) && (is_array($operand2))) {
  3407.                 foreach($operand2 as $x => $operandData) {
  3408.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.$this->_showValue($operand1).' '.$operation.' '.$this->_showValue($operandData));
  3409.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operand1,$operandData,$operation,$stack);
  3410.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  3411.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  3412.                 }
  3413.             } else {
  3414.                 if (!$recursingArrays) { self::_checkMatrixOperands($operand1,$operand2,2); }
  3415.                 foreach($operand1 as $x => $operandData) {
  3416.                     $this->_writeDebug('Evaluating '.$this->_showValue($operandData).' '.$operation.' '.$this->_showValue($operand2[$x]));
  3417.                     $this->_executeBinaryComparisonOperation($cellID,$operandData,$operand2[$x],$operation,$stack,true);
  3418.                     $r = $stack->pop();
  3419.                     $result[$x] = $r['value'];
  3420.                 }
  3421.             }
  3422.             //    Log the result details
  3423.             $this->_writeDebug('Evaluation Result is '.$this->_showTypeDetails($result));
  3424.             //    And push the result onto the stack
  3425.             $stack->push('Array',$result);
  3426.             return true;
  3427.         }
  3428.  
  3429.         //    Simple validate the two operands if they are string values
  3430.         if (is_string($operand1) && $operand1 > '' && $operand1{0} == '"') { $operand1 = self::_unwrapResult($operand1); }
  3431.         if (is_string($operand2) && $operand2 > '' && $operand2{0} == '"') { $operand2 = self::_unwrapResult($operand2); }
  3432.  
  3433.         //    execute the necessary operation
  3434.         switch ($operation) {
  3435.             //    Greater than
  3436.             case '>':
  3437.                 $result = ($operand1 > $operand2);
  3438.                 break;
  3439.             //    Less than
  3440.             case '<':
  3441.                 $result = ($operand1 < $operand2);
  3442.                 break;
  3443.             //    Equality
  3444.             case '=':
  3445.                 $result = ($operand1 == $operand2);
  3446.                 break;
  3447.             //    Greater than or equal
  3448.             case '>=':
  3449.                 $result = ($operand1 >= $operand2);
  3450.                 break;
  3451.             //    Less than or equal
